Test-NoPlan

A small test module to ensure all test scripts specify the correct number of
tests to be run rather than using 'no_plan'.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Test::NoPlan

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Test-NoPlan

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Test-NoPlan

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Test-NoPlan

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Test-NoPlan/

    Source (git)
        git://github.com/duncs/perl-test-noplan.git

